# 🚗 U.S. Accident Analysis  

## 📌 Project Overview  
This project focuses on analyzing **U.S. accident data** to identify trends, risk factors, and patterns that impact road safety. The goal is to extract meaningful insights using **Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA), data visualization, and machine learning models**.  

## 🔍 Dataset  
The dataset used for this analysis is **US Accidents (2016 - 2023)**, which includes accident records from across 49 U.S. states. You can access the dataset here:  
📂 **[US Accidents Dataset on Kaggle](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/sobhanmoosavi/us-accidents/)**  

## 🔬 Technologies Used  
- **Programming Language:** Python  
- **Libraries & Frameworks:**  
  - **Data Analysis & Cleaning:** Pandas, NumPy  
  - **Visualization:** Matplotlib, Seaborn, Power BI  
  - **Machine Learning (if applied):** Scikit-Learn  

## 📊 Key Insights  
- Trends in accident frequency across different states  
- Impact of weather, time, and location on accident severity  
- Data-driven insights to improve road safety  

